channel.title: Where can i delete an object?
channel.description:
Want to delete a lever in evil bobs room (the one where on real runescape you pop balloons to get keys to exit random event) anyway not too sure where i can delete it at. I know the object id and co-ords and tried looking in objectmanager.java. Sorry if this is basic, im still learning =p
[pi]

item.title: Where can i delete an object?
item.dc:creator: @avirunes avirunes
item.description:
@avirunes wrote:

[quote=“rash, post:5, topic:380865”][quote author=avirunes link=topic=476690.msg3486751#msg3486751 date=1296634737]
yea its not there because its not a custom spawned item, its one that spawns there in real rs
[/quote]

c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(-1, xcoord, ycoord, 1, 10);

the -1 means remove the object that is there.[/quote]

ooh, sorry, thats embaressing on my part lol. Thanks will try it now
